[src:mid-air-collision/aeroflot-accidents-and-incidents] During a 1931 overhaul for conversion to an airliner, the right wing was improperly repaired.
[src:mid-air-collision/aeroflot-accidents-and-incidents] , the mechanic informed the pilot of an oil leak on the right engine.
[src:mid-air-collision/aeroflot-accidents-and-incidents] The pilot began descending and decided to divert to Oktyabrskoye Airfield.
[src:mid-air-collision/aeroflot-accidents-and-incidents] with both remaining engines at full power, the aircraft rolled to the right, stalled and crashed in a forest.
[src:mid-air-collision/aeroflot-accidents-and-incidents] The oil leak was caused by a failed hydraulic pump.
[src:mid-air-collision/aeroflot-accidents-and-incidents] The aircraft was operating a Irkutsk-Bodaibo cargo service.
[src:mid-air-collision/aeroflot-accidents-and-incidents] from Kirensk the weather worsened and visibility was poor from falling snow.
[src:mid-air-collision/aeroflot-accidents-and-incidents] The pilot descended, ostensibly to remain visual contact with the ground.
[src:mid-air-collision/aeroflot-accidents-and-incidents] The aircraft was operating a Baku-Tiflis (now Tbilisi) passenger service.
[src:mid-air-collision/aeroflot-accidents-and-incidents] En route to Ganzhda and Yevlakh the pilot encountered poor visibility due to fog.
