[src:mid-air-collision/aeroflot-accidents-and-incidents] The aircraft was operating a Moscow-Kharkiv mail flight.
[src:mid-air-collision/aeroflot-accidents-and-incidents] Approaching Podolsk, the weather deteriorated and the pilot decided to return to Moscow, but the weather was also poor there.
[src:mid-air-collision/aeroflot-accidents-and-incidents] , the aircraft struck an antenna, partially tearing off the right wing.
[src:mid-air-collision/aeroflot-accidents-and-incidents] The aircraft was operating a Sverdlovsk (now Yekaterinburg)-Yanaul-Kazan passenger service.
[src:mid-air-collision/aeroflot-accidents-and-incidents] , the weather worsened with snow showers, although the weather forecast called for rain.
[src:mid-air-collision/aeroflot-accidents-and-incidents] The pilot later decided on an emergency landing near Kontuganovo.
[src:mid-air-collision/aeroflot-accidents-and-incidents] , the left wing struck a tall tree and the aircraft crashed.
[src:mid-air-collision/aeroflot-accidents-and-incidents] The pilot died of his injuries a few hours later.
[src:mid-air-collision/aeroflot-accidents-and-incidents] , the pilot lost control while performing stunts.
[src:mid-air-collision/aeroflot-accidents-and-incidents] The aircraft entered a dive and crashed.
[src:mid-air-collision/aeroflot-accidents-and-incidents] The inexperienced pilot had become disorientated.
[src:mid-air-collision/aeroflot-accidents-and-incidents] The two aircraft were operating a training flight when they collided.
[src:mid-air-collision/aeroflot-accidents-and-incidents] Cause attributed to errors of both pilots.
[src:mid-air-collision/aeroflot-accidents-and-incidents] The ANT-9 was on a test flight, and after 13 minutes, the pilot decided to return to the airport.
[src:mid-air-collision/aeroflot-accidents-and-incidents] On final approach, the aircraft collided with a Polikarpov U-2 (CCCP-S227) that had been completing a local flight.
[src:mid-air-collision/aeroflot-accidents-and-incidents] Both aircraft crashed, killing both pilots of the U-2; all on board the ANT-9 only suffered minor injuries.
[src:mid-air-collision/aeroflot-accidents-and-incidents] The aircraft was operating a charter flight from Moscow to Feodosia.
[src:mid-air-collision/aeroflot-accidents-and-incidents] En route, the aircraft encountered bad weather.
[src:mid-air-collision/aeroflot-accidents-and-incidents] The aircraft took off from Moscow on a cargo flight.
[src:mid-air-collision/aeroflot-accidents-and-incidents] , the crew encountered vibration and stability problems and decided to return to Moscow.
[src:mid-air-collision/aeroflot-accidents-and-incidents] the aircraft entered an uncontrolled descent and crashed.
[src:mid-air-collision/aeroflot-accidents-and-incidents] The tail had separated due to unexplained vibration; the exact cause of the crash was never determined.
[src:mid-air-collision/aeroflot-accidents-and-incidents] The pilot attempted to find a spot for a forced landing but the aircraft nosed down and crashed and caught fire.
[src:mid-air-collision/aeroflot-accidents-and-incidents] The cause of the engine problem was not determined, but a faulty carburetor was blamed and the loss of control was caused by pilot error.
[src:mid-air-collision/aeroflot-accidents-and-incidents] The aircraft was operating a training flight.
[src:mid-air-collision/aeroflot-accidents-and-incidents] Five minutes after takeoff, the aircraft entered a high-speed descent.
[src:mid-air-collision/aeroflot-accidents-and-incidents] The crew attempted to regain control, but the aircraft struck ground and crashed upside down.
[src:mid-air-collision/aeroflot-accidents-and-incidents] The aircraft was on a Moscow-Tashkent delivery flight.
[src:mid-air-collision/aeroflot-accidents-and-incidents] During the Samara-Orenburg leg, the engine failed and the crew made an emergency landing.
[src:mid-air-collision/aeroflot-accidents-and-incidents] Due to poor weather, technical problems and awaiting fuel from Orenburg, the crew was stuck for 18 days.
[src:mid-air-collision/aeroflot-accidents-and-incidents] Following repairs, the aircraft took off to return to Samara.
[src:mid-air-collision/aeroflot-accidents-and-incidents] While attempting an emergency landing, the aircraft stalled and crashed.
[src:mid-air-collision/aeroflot-accidents-and-incidents] The aircraft was operating a Moscow-Leningrad mail flight.
[src:mid-air-collision/aeroflot-accidents-and-incidents] A few minutes after takeoff, weather conditions worsened with low ceiling and intermittent snow.
[src:mid-air-collision/aeroflot-accidents-and-incidents] the aircraft entered a right turn, descended and crashed.
[src:mid-air-collision/aeroflot-accidents-and-incidents] The aircraft took off from Akytubinsk on a mail flight.
[src:mid-air-collision/aeroflot-accidents-and-incidents] Ten minutes after takeoff the pilot decided to return because he thought there was a loss of hydraulic pressure.
[src:mid-air-collision/aeroflot-accidents-and-incidents] Due to an incorrect approach configuration, the pilot landed with a tailwind and the aircraft struck a parked U-2SP (CCCP-Л1018) after landing.
[src:mid-air-collision/aeroflot-accidents-and-incidents] The pilot escaped with only minor injuries.
[src:mid-air-collision/aeroflot-accidents-and-incidents] The aircraft was operating a Novosibirsk-Omsk mail flight.
[src:mid-air-collision/aeroflot-accidents-and-incidents] After passing over Tatarsk, weather conditions worsened with low ceiling, heavy rain and strong winds.
[src:mid-air-collision/aeroflot-accidents-and-incidents] After entering clouds, the pilot became disorientated and attempted to return to Tatarsk, but the local beacon was not working due to poor weather.
[src:mid-air-collision/aeroflot-accidents-and-incidents] While attempting an emergency landing, the aircraft crashed.
[src:mid-air-collision/aeroflot-accidents-and-incidents] over the valley of Oka, weather deteriorated with havy clouds, drizzle and low ceiling.
[src:mid-air-collision/aeroflot-accidents-and-incidents] After completing two turns, the pilot did not realize that he was flying too low and the aircraft crashed.
[src:mid-air-collision/aeroflot-accidents-and-incidents] The aircraft was operating a Mineralnye Vody-Armavir-Rostov mail flight.
[src:mid-air-collision/aeroflot-accidents-and-incidents] Following technical problems, the pilot was forced to stay overnight in Armavir due to poor weather.
[src:mid-air-collision/aeroflot-accidents-and-incidents] The pilot departed Armavir, but while approaching Kutschevka, the aircraft encountered fog and the pilot decided to turn around.
[src:mid-air-collision/aeroflot-accidents-and-incidents] While turning around and apparently attempting to maintain visual contact with the ground, the aircraft lost altitude and crashed.
[src:mid-air-collision/aeroflot-accidents-and-incidents] The aircraft was operating an Alma-Ata (now Almaty)-Karaganda-Taldykorgan-Balkhash passenger service.
[src:mid-air-collision/aeroflot-accidents-and-incidents] On approach to Taldykorgan, the pilot made a series of mistakes and violations and landed the aircraft in a crosswind and the aircraft touched down on one landing gear.
[src:mid-air-collision/aeroflot-accidents-and-incidents] A go-around was made and the aircraft landed safely.
[src:mid-air-collision/aeroflot-accidents-and-incidents] Approaching Balkhash, the winds picked up.
[src:mid-air-collision/aeroflot-accidents-and-incidents] The aircraft lost altitude and touched the ground with the left wing and then hit the ground first with the nose and left engine and then the right engine and right wing. breaking off both engines.
[src:mid-air-collision/aeroflot-accidents-and-incidents] The aircraft was operating a Irkutsk-Bodaibo passenger service.
[src:mid-air-collision/aeroflot-accidents-and-incidents] and made a 180 degree turn to begin the takeoff.
