[src:mid-air-collision/aeroflot-accidents-and-incidents] En route weather worsened and visibility was poor due to snow and fog.
[src:mid-air-collision/aeroflot-accidents-and-incidents] The pilot continued instead of returning to Balkhash.
[src:mid-air-collision/aeroflot-accidents-and-incidents] After flying at night for four hours the aircraft struck the side of Mount Kyzyltas.
[src:mid-air-collision/aeroflot-accidents-and-incidents] To complicate matters, Balkhash Airport received an erroneous message that the aircraft had landed in Karaganda and it took two days to realize the information was wrong.
[src:mid-air-collision/aeroflot-accidents-and-incidents] The exhausted pilot had made a navigation error.
[src:mid-air-collision/aeroflot-accidents-and-incidents] The aircraft was operating the first leg of an Irkutsk-Ulan-Ude–Mogocha cargo flight, but never arrived at Ulan-Ude.
[src:mid-air-collision/aeroflot-accidents-and-incidents] The steps of the two sets of footprints showed nothing unusual.
[src:mid-air-collision/aeroflot-accidents-and-incidents] Evidence of the two relieving themselves was found, then the footprints stopped at hidden ice holes, where the crew probably fell through the ice.
